The press briefing by Press Secretary Jay Carney on December 11, 2012 covered various topics including the fiscal cliff negotiations and the situation in Syria. Carney emphasized that the President has put forward detailed spending cuts and revenue proposals, while Republicans have not provided specific proposals on revenue. He also discussed the need for a balanced approach to deficit reduction that includes both spending cuts and revenue increases. On Syria, Carney stated that the United States stands with the Syrian people and that any transition process should result in a peaceful, unified, democratic Syria without Bashar al Assad. He also addressed concerns about chemical weapons in Syria and reiterated the warning to the Assad regime about their potential use.